Data availability

            Ice-free land and sea-level change projections from this study are available via Dryad at https://doi.org/10.5061/dryad.f7m0cfz9j (ref. 93). Antarctic and Greenland ice sheet models50,51 used for sea level projections can be accessed via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7773727 (ref. 94) and https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5880517 (ref. 95), respectively. The ETOPO 2022 Global Relief Model used for ice-free land exposure calculations can be accessed at https://doi.org/10.25921/fd45-gt74 (ref. 96). The figures were generated using the Generic Mapping Tools97 and ParaView98.
          Code availability

            The code needed to reproduce the results and figures presented in this study is available via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7126141 (ref. 99). Procedures for reproducing the ice-free land emergence projections using the sea-level change projections and initial bedrock topography are outlined in the Methods.
